dist: show TOTP even if vconsole setup fails

Change Requires= to Wants= for systemd-vconsole-setup.service. This allows
showing a code even if the vconsole setup fails (for example, because of a bad
font or bad keymap).

Signed-off-by: Romain “Artefact2” Dal Maso <romain.dalmaso@artefact2.com>

lgtm: fix tpm2-tss build

Fix the issue on bootstrap by using a git clone, fixes:
"fatal: not a git repository (or any of the parent directories): .git"

Signed-off-by: William Roberts <william.c.roberts@intel.com>

VERSION: add version file

Generate the version file with bootstrap and include in the DIST tarball
so endusers can call autoreconf on a dist tarball which doesn't have
git. This alleviates git describe errors on release tarballs in the
autoreconf case.

build: provide default value of systemdsystemunitdir for make distcheck

The same issue that has been fixed in commit
cb6f7bebec5ca6efd6933a23d9229b568dbe1a8e ("build: fix make distcheck without
sudo") for dracutmodulesdir has resurfaced for systemdsystemunitdir: since it
is derived using pkg-config, it doesn't respect ${prefix}, making make
distcheck fail (or install directly to the system directory instead of DESTDIR
if invoked as root). Provide a value for systemdsystemunitdir derived from
${prefix} that is used for distcheck.
